description: From Middle English chykwed, chykewode, chike wed, chikewed, chekwede, a variant of chykynwede, chekyn-wede, cheken-wede (literally “chicken-weed”), equivalent to chick +‎ weed.

definitionGroups.group: Any of several small-leaved herbs of the genera Cerastium and Stellaria.

entries.meaning: especially common chickweed, Stellaria media, a common, edible weed in North America and Europe.
examples: I look at the little sprigs of chickweed trembling among the bean shoots and I am strangely moved. Such steadfastness! Such yearning! They want to live too. That is all they ask: to have their little moment in the world.
